{"cursor":"3055","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox scientist |name = Charles Hill |image = |image_size = 160px |caption =\n|birth_date = |nationality = United States |ethnicity = |workplaces = Yale\nUniversity |fields = Humanities |alma_mater = Brown University University\nof Pennsylvania }}\n\n\n'Charles Hill' (born April 28, 1936) is the Diplomat-in-Residence and a\nlecturer in International Studies at Yale University. [http://www.hoover.org/bios/hill.html] A career foreign\nservice officer, Mr. Hill was a senior adviser to George Shultz, Henry\nKissinger, and Ronald Reagan, as well as Boutros Boutros-Ghali, the sixth Secretary-\nGeneral of the United Nations. At Yale, he teaches, along with Paul Kennedy and\nJohn Gaddis, the seminar \"Studies in Grand Strategy\", a rigorous\ninterdisciplinary study of leadership, statecraft and diplomacy. He also\nteaches students enrolled in the Directed Studies program. Beginning in 2006,\nHill offered a new course, Oratory in Statecraft. Not since Rollin G.\nOsterweis, who taught \"The History and Practice of American Oratory\", had\noratory been taught at Yale.\n\nHill received a B.A. from Brown University in 1960, a J.D. and an M.A. in\nAmerican Studies from the University of Pennsylvania in 1960 and 1961, respectively. http://jackson.yale.edu/hill-\n0/ He is a recipient of the Superior Honor Award from the State\nDepartment, the Presidential Distinguished Service Award, and the Secretary of\nState's Medal. http://www.hoover.org/fellows/10191/ He holds an\nhonorary doctorate of laws from Rowan\nUniversity. http://www.hoover.org/fellows/10191/\n\nHill is a research fellow at Stanford University's Hoover Institution. Hill is\nalso a Project for the New American Century (PNAC) signatory. Hill served as\nChief Foreign Policy Advisor to Rudy Giuliani, a Republican candidate for the\n2008 presidential election.\n","linknr":142,"url":"Charles_Hill_(diplomat)","recorded":1376418507,"links":["/w/index.php?t